description: Karol Nawrocki, the right-wing candidate in Poland’s presidential runoff election, won on Sunday night and will be the country’s next president.  Nawrocki defeated Rafał Trzaskowski by the slimmest of margins, winning 50.89% of the vote. Trzaskowski, the liberal candidate and current mayor of Warsaw, received 49.11% of the vote, according to the Associated Press. The […]
title: Conservative candidate Karol Nawrocki wins Poland’s presidential runoff election

author: Zach LaChance
description: China blasted U.S. Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth‘s speech at a defense forum in Singapore over the weekend, accusing him of trying “to sow discord” after he warned of a potentially “imminent” threat to Taiwan. In a statement on Sunday, the Chinese Foreign Ministry rebuked Hegseth’s remarks, saying the defense secretary invoked the “Cold War mentality […]
title: China warns US ‘must never play with fire’ on Taiwan in rebuke of Hegseth speech

author: Washington Examiner
description: President Donald Trump’s decision to green-light a restructured deal between US Steel and Japanese-owned Nippon Steel was a turnaround for him and perhaps for American manufacturing. title: Trump’s US Steel deal is a win for America

description: FDA Commissioner Marty Makary defended the U.S. federal health agencies recent removal of the COVID-19 vaccine from the recommended immunization schedule for healthy children and pregnant women, saying the decision to get the shot should instead be made with their doctor. title: FDA chief defends move to stop recommending COVID vaccine for healthy children, pregnant women
